profile_data.summary: Chris Capitelli earned his Real Estate License in 1991. Chris sells residential properties on Long Island from Montauk to Manhattan. In 2018 Chris has taken on an additional role as Broker/Owner of Exit Realty Trailblazers in Lancaster and Berlin, NH. With 2 Offices in Northern New Hampshire, Exit Realty Trailblazers is more than confident that they can handle all of your real estate needs. Chris and Exit Realty use the latest internet technologies to market and find homes at an expert level. Chris understands that the purchase of a home is often the largest purchase a person will make in their lifetime. He believes Realtors have an obligation to be well educated to provide the level of service and protection his clients deserve. Chris is constantly furthering his knowledge and has recently earned the designation of Certified HAFA Short Sale Specialist. His constant dedication to service and work ethic has earned him numerous awards throughout the years. Chris has had the honor of being recognized in Real Trends Who’s Who in Residential Real Estate and received many other awards such as Pinnacle Award (Ranked #3 in sales on LI ) and the prestigious Shining Star Award from National Sales Trainer Floyd Wickman. Chris is an active member in his church and has volunteered at the AHRC Special Olympics and Habitat for Humanity. Exit Realty has donated over $2 Million to the charity and built over 15 Habitat Homes. Chris understands the stresses and hassles involved in the buying, selling and relo process and he strives to alleviate these concerns for his clients as much as possible. Chris feels that the best path to his success is to help others get what they need to realize their success. Because of his track record of accountability, education, attention to detail and personal attention, Chris’ clients become customers for life. He can’t wait to provide you with the same outstanding service he has provided to his past clients, making you a customer for life as well.

profile_data.summary:
About Our Team: 

As a Broker Associate & Seniors Real Estate Specialist, Jeri has been selling real estate in this area since 1993 and has been the TOP selling agent since 1995.  I moved to TOLLHOUSE from Thousand Oaks, CA in 1991.  My family and friends thought that I was crazy leaving such a nice area and moving to the country and they all thought that I would be back in 6 months.  Well, all these years later, I am still here and loving it every day. My clients are extremely important to me and therefore I strive to give them the best service possible and make myself available to them at all times.  

To better assist these special people, we have Kelli Crawford that specializes in working with home buyers and David Sheppard who facilitates our paperwork, inspections, and assists buyers too!

Our foothills are so awesome that you cannot possibly tire of looking at all the beauty that surrounds you here.  The schools are great, people are friendly and the area is safe.  

Should you want to look in the city, we can assist you there as well.  Fresno and Clovis are in our "backdoor".

We hope that you find our website to be a great source of information and visit often. We will always be available for personal service by phone or email, so feel free to contact us with questions any time! If you are looking to BUY or SELL a home or land, you have come to the right place.  

Call or email us any time! Selling or Buying is probably going to be one of the largest financial transactions you will face.  Don't face it alone.  Put the knowledge and experience of our combined 32 years behind you.   Better yet, let us do the work and worrying so you don't have to! 

Sincerely,

position.title: Broker/Owner
position.description:
Everyday Living Realty, LLC is located in Charlotte, NC.  We provide real estate services to residential and commercial buyers and sellers.  This company utilizes all the technological advances available in the real estate industry to assist home buyers and sellers locate and sell properties quickly.  Our speciality is to unveil the mysteries of real estate and pride ourselves on keeping the process clear and simple.  Here is what we offer:

• Professional residential and commercial real estate brokerage services to buyers and sellers in Charlotte, NC and surround cities. 
• Educate clients on current market trends and how it will impact their bottom-line.
• Maintain strong working relationships with industry partners (Home inspectors, brokers, agents, lenders, appraisers, attorneys, title companies, pest inspectors, cleaning services and moving specialists).  
• Uphold the following duties to our clients:  Obedience, Loyalty, Full disclosure, Confidentiality, Accounting and Reasonable Skill, Care and Diligence.
• Prepare market analysis reports for buyers and sellers based on recent sales activities in the local market.
• Conduct pre-purchase consultations, listing presentations, home buyer seminars, and investment seminars.

If you are in Charlotte or relocating to Charlotte and looking for an agent, contact Everyday Living Realty, LLC at (704) 927-1496 or visit our website at www.EverydayLivingRealty.com.  Let us get you moving!

items.title: Chesapeake Flyboarding
items.description: The Flyboard, invented by jetski racing champion Franky Zapata, is essentially a water-powered jetpack with bolted-in shoes that can be strapped to your feet, enabling users to skate around at a height of nine meters. Like the Jetlev jetpack, it's powered through a hose attachment that connects to a jetski's thruster. Propulsion is generated as the force of the water runs up through the hose and shoots out from the bottom of the board.

position.title: Sr Sales Engineer
position.description:
As a Sr. Sales Engineer with TrueFort, I help maintain relationships with our customers by adding value to their security needs through a consultative approach.

I help our customers save time, money, and resources by giving them the ability to protect data cener and cloud application workloads to make zero trust possible.

The TrueFort Platform is the only solution instilling the confidence to protect workloads across all production environments. By reducing the impact of security incidents, we increase your overall business resilience, shrink your exploitable attack surface, and enable you to take immediate action against live attacks.

We protect runtime environments in six key ways:

- MicroSegmentation – intelligently baseline normal, high-volume activity within and between workloads, limiting future behavior to what should be trusted.  
- Service Account Behavior Analytics – identify, monitor, and learn trusted user account usage patterns.
- Cloud Workload Protection – secure workloads by dynamically adapting to unusual activities detected across on-premises and cloud workloads.
- File Integrity Monitoring - validate any unexpected changes to discover novel malicious activity.
- Workload Hardening – use adaptive configuration policy monitoring against CIS and similar standards, with immediate notification when a compliance change occurs.
- Container and Kubernetes Security – protect containers from compromise by baselining runtime behavior to find anomalies and respond in real-time.

If you are ready to protect workloads of all forms, contact me today.

Specialties: MicroSegmentation | Service Accounts | Cloud Workload Protection | Workload Hardening (CIS) | File Integrity Monitoring (FIM)

Managing Security at the Speed of Business

AlgoSec is the market leader for security policy management, enabling organizations to simplify and automate security operations in evolving data centers and networks.  AlgoSec allows for faster security provisioning of business applications, streamlined change management, continuous compliance and tighter security. 
AlgoSec’s application-centric approach orchestrates the management of complex policies across firewalls and related network devices, aligning IT teams for improved business agility.
